    "what_description": "Nephrodium lobbii is an extinct species of fern that belonged to the family Polypodiaceae. It is characterized by its ovate to lanceolate sterile pinnules with entire margins and its pinnate frond with a long stipe. The frond typically reaches a length of 30-50 cm and a width of 5-8 cm, with the fertile pinnules being smaller and having shorter stalks. The plant is known to have been found in the tropical forests of Asia, particularly in China and Japan, and is typically associated with humid and shaded environments. Its extinct status is due to the loss of its native habitats and the absence of fossil records dating back to the late Miocene to early Pliocene epochs.",
