    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Nephrodium lobbii are fever and cough, often resulting from respiratory tract infections, which the plant's flavonoids and saponins have been shown to inhibit. Nephrodium lobbii has also been found to exhibit anti-inflammatory properties, making it effective in reducing pain and swelling associated with conditions such as arthritis. The plant's antiseptic properties make it useful in treating wounds and preventing infections, including skin infections and septicemia. Furthermore, Nephrodium lobbii has been used to treat gastrointestinal issues, such as diarrhea and dysentery, due to its ability to reduce inflammation in the digestive tract. Additionally, the plant's expectorant properties make it useful in treating bronchitis and other respiratory conditions characterized by excessive mucus production.",
