    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Nephrodium lobbii are its anti-inflammatory activity, which helps alleviate pain and reduce inflammation in the body. This is attributed to the presence of saponins, bioactive compounds that have been shown to exhibit anti-inflammatory properties. Additionally, the plant's antifungal and antibacterial properties make it an effective treatment for various infections, with flavonoids contributing to its antimicrobial activity. Furthermore, Nephrodium lobbii has been found to have antioxidant properties, which can help protect cells from damage caused by free radicals, and terpenoids are responsible for its antioxidant effects. Its antispasmodic properties also allow it to be used to treat conditions such as asthma and bronchitis, with volatile oils contributing to its antispasmodic activity.",
