    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Nephrodium lobbii are flavonoids such as 7-hydroxy-3,3',4'-trimethoxyflavone and 7-hydroxy-3,4'-dimethoxyflavone which have been shown to exhibit antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties, reducing oxidative stress and inflammation in the body. The plant also contains triterpenoids like 3-oxo-olean-12-en-29-oic acid, which has been found to possess immunomodulatory and antimicrobial activities. Additionally, Nephrodium lobbii contains phenolic acids like protocatechuic acid and ferulic acid, which have been reported to exhibit anti-cancer and antioxidant properties. These constituents work synergistically to provide a range of therapeutic benefits, making Nephrodium lobbii a valuable resource for traditional medicine. The exact mechanisms by which these constituents exert their effects are not fully understood, but their bioactive properties have been well-documented in scientific studies.",
