    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Nephrodium lobbii are tincture, infusion, tea, decoction, and salve. Nephrodium lobbii tincture is made by soaking the plant's aerial parts in a solvent like ethanol or glycerin, extracting its bioactive compounds. Infusion is prepared by steeping dried leaves or young shoots in hot water, releasing flavonoids, phenolic acids, and other secondary metabolites. Decoction is a more robust extraction method, involving boiling the plant material in water to release its stored compounds, including alkaloids and glycosides. A salve made from Nephrodium lobbii is a topical application, combining the plant's extracts with a carrier oil to aid in skin and wound healing, potentially benefiting from its anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties.",
